  "prompt": "What will happen if you connect phase and ground?",
  "response": "If you connect phase (live/hot) and ground wires directly:\n\n1. Immediate consequences:\n- A large electrical current will flow\n- Circuit breaker or fuse will trip immediately\n- Potential for electrical sparks\n- Risk of short circuit\n\n2. Safety risks:\n- Potential electrical fire\n- Risk of electric shock\n- Damage to electrical equipment\n- Potential personal injury\n\n3. Technical details:\n- Ground provides a low-resistance path to earth\n- Creates a direct short circuit\n- Extremely high current flow\n- Voltage will essentially be zero across the connection\n\n4. Recommended action:\n- Never intentionally connect phase and ground\n- Only qualified electricians should handle electrical connections\n- Always follow electrical safety protocols\n\n5. Protective mechanisms:\n- Circuit breakers will disconnect power\n- Ground fault circuit interrupters (GFCI) will trip\n- Prevents sustained electrical fault\n\nIt's crucial to treat electrical connections with caution and respect professional electrical standards.",
